        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>May 28th 1847</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr Isaac. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">A temporary absence from<lb/>
                <placeName>N. Orleans</placeName>, to <placeName>Vicksburg</placeName> and very
                active employment since my return<lb/> leaving me very little time of my own, are
                the only excuses I have<lb/> to offer for allowing your kind favor of
                    <date>19th</date> ultimo to be so long unanswered.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I have as yet been unable to procure any<lb/> suitable person to
                whom I can entrust <del>the</del> with proper confidence your<lb/> interest here,
                &amp; the time for my departure to <placeName>Kentucky</placeName> (say<lb/>
                <date>10th</date> next month) will leave me so little time to find a<lb/> proper
                person that I am a loss what to do in the matter.<lb/> I shall be absent all summer,
                and am sorry for your<lb/> sake that this is the case as nothing would give me<lb/>
                more pleasure than to further your welfare, knowing as I<lb/> do how essential it is
                for the interest of our religion,<lb/> I will look out for some one who will
                undertake it<lb/> &amp; collect the subscriptions, I believe I have in my<lb/>
                possession the amt of <persName>Brown's</persName>subscription 1<hi rend="sup"
                    >st</hi>. Year 3$<lb/>
                <persName>A Block</persName> up to <date>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> April 47</date> =
                3$ &amp; one other subscriber<lb/> whose name I forget 3$ this is all the money in
                my hand<lb/> Address me here with instructions &amp; in my absence my<lb/> Father
                will attend to them.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><persName>Mr. Kursheedt</persName> does not recommend the
                advertise<lb/>-ment of the sale of Books &amp; his views generally being good</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>I have refrained from doing so, there is such an apathy<lb/> here as to foode for the
                soul, that there is no sale or<lb/> demand for anything of the kinde, Its all money!
                Money<lb/> Money!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have seen nothing of <persName>Rabbi Cohen</persName> of
                        <placeName><sic>Helon</sic>, Palestine</placeName><lb/> but will be glad to
                state your wishes to the gentlemen of<lb/> our Congregation here. I stated to
                    <persName>Mr Levy</persName> your instruct<lb/>-ions &amp; suppose he has
                written you—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I am dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">D. C. Labatt</persName>
            </p>
